    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        private void initialize()
        Initialization of some parameters and operations that require multiple lines of code. Done outside of the constructor for readability purpose.

      • switchDirection

        private void switchDirection(java.lang.String nextDirection)
        Changes the current direction of the snake. If next direction is the same as or opposite of the current direction the method returns without making changes.
        Parameters:
        nextDirection - The desired direction of the snake.

      • reverseMovement

        private void reverseMovement()
        Reverses the movement of the snake. If the snake is more than 1 tile long the direction of the snake is retrieved by the position of the last 2 snake tiles(the tail).

      • moveSnake

        private void moveSnake()
        Moves the snake with 1 tile. The method also checks the type of the next tile and takes action accordingly.
        • If direction is Up - next tile is [x-1][y];
        • if direction is Down - next tile is [x+1][y];
        • if direction is Left - next tile is [x][y-1];
        • if direction is Right - next tile is [x][y+1];

      • changeTileType

        private void changeTileType(game.Tile tile,
                            game.TileType newType)
        Changes the tile type of the given tile. The GUI is updated afterwards.
        Parameters:
        tile - The tile to get updated.
        newType - The new tile type.

      • die

        Returns:

      • spawnFruit

        private void spawnFruit()
        Spawns a fruit on the game field. The location of the fruit is a random location currently covered with grass.
